Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Stanford University
Description: Considered the Ivy League of the West Coast, it is a University that has a great academic and athletic reputation, located in Palo Alto.

Name: San Diego Zoo
Description: One of the most famous Zoo's n the world. Located in Balboa Park in San Diego, it houses thousands of animals and is a place for rehabilitation for animals.

Name: Knott's Berry Farm
Description: An amusement park located in Southern California. Its main attractions are The Silver Bullet, The Boomerang, The Accelerator and Ghost Rider.

Name: La Jolla Cove
Description: Located north of San Diego City, La Jolla (considered the Jewel of San Diego) is a beautiful place to snorkel, scuba dive, kayak or just relax on vacation.

Name: Golden Gate Bridge
Description: An extremely famous tourist location located in the Golden Gate in San Francisco. Built in 1937, it spans 1.6 km and was the largest and tallest suspension bridge at the time of its creation.
